t: Psalm 147
Praise*p ye the Lord:*s for it is good to sing praises unto our God; for it is pleasant; and praise is comely.
The*p Lord*s doth build up Jerusalem: he gathereth together the outcasts of Israel.
He*p healeth the broken in heart, and bindeth up their wounds.
He*p telleth the number of the stars; he calleth them all by their names.
Great*p is our Lord, and of great power: his understanding is infinite.
The*p Lord*s lifteth up the meek: he casteth the wicked down to the ground.
Sing*p unto the Lord*s with thanksgiving; sing praise upon the harp unto our God:
Who*p covereth the heaven with clouds, who prepareth rain for the earth, who maketh grass to grow upon the mountains.
He*p giveth to the beast his food, and to the young ravens which cry.
He*p delighteth not in the strength of the horse: he taketh not pleasure in the legs of a man.
The*p Lord*s taketh pleasure in them that fear him, in those that hope in his mercy.
Praise*p the Lord,*s O Jerusalem; praise thy God, O Zion.
For*p he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates; he hath blessed thy children within thee.
He*p maketh peace in thy borders, and filleth thee with the finest of the wheat.
He*p sendeth forth his commandment upon earth: his word runneth very swiftly.
He*p giveth snow like wool: he scattereth the hoarfrost like ashes.
He*p casteth forth his ice like morsels: who can stand before his cold?
He*p sendeth out his word, and melteth them: he causeth his wind to blow, and the waters flow.
He*p sheweth his word unto Jacob, his statutes and his judgments unto Israel.
He*p hath not dealt so with any nation: and as for his judgments, they have not known them. Praise ye the Lord.*s
